adjectives.description: infantlike (comparative more infantlike, superlative most infantlike)

examples: c. 1608–1609 (date written),  William Shakespeare,  “The Tragedy of Coriolanus”, in  Mr. William Shakespeares Comedies, Histories, & Tragedies […] (First Folio), London:  […]  Isaac Iaggard, and Ed[ward] Blount, published 1623, →OCLC, [Act II, scene i], page 8, column 2:I know you can doe very little alone, for your / helpes are many, or elſe your actions would growe won- / derous ſingle : your abilities are to Infant-like, for dooing / much alone.
